&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NUCE E 497I: Fuel Performance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Nuclear fuel behavior under normal operation and accident conditions. &lt;br /&gt;
Material aspects, thermal performance, and burnup effects. &lt;br /&gt;
Testing, modeling and associated uncertainties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This course is designed to function both as a technical elective for undergraduate students and graduate course in nuclear engineering. &lt;br /&gt;
The course will be open for both resident and distance students.&lt;/p&gt;
